This paper discusses the design of effective model-based reinforcement learning algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of models in policy optimization, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data generation and bias, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
